<td tEditID="c1r1" style=" background-color:#FFFFFF; bEditID:r3st1; color:#000000; bLabel:main; font-size:12pt; font-family:arial;" aEditID="c1r1" locked="0" >
<![CDATA[<div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2">Dear {!Contact.Name},</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2">&nbsp;</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2">Thank you for your interest in joining <b>CASS {!Case.Country__c}</b>.</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2">&nbsp;</font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2">You can now apply to join a CASS operation through our Customer Portal – Online services via the new '<b><font color="#3333ff">Join BSP/CASS</font></b>' &nbsp;functionality. &nbsp;It will allow you to:</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><ul><li><span style="font-size: small;">Initiate online an application to join a CASS operation</span></li><li><span style="font-size: small;">Eliminate the need to send the CASS Joining Form in paper format</span></li><li><span style="font-size: small;">Add or correct any information in the Online CASS Joining Form when necessary&nbsp;</span></li><li><span style="font-size: small;">View the status of your application</span></li><li><span style="font-size: small;">Communicate directly with the IATA Representative handling your process.&nbsp;</span></li></ul></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-size: small;"><br></span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-size: small;"><b><font color="#000099">A. Starting your Joining Process:</font></b>&nbsp;</span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-size: small;"><br></span></div><div><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: small;">&nbsp; a) Access our&nbsp;</span><span style="font-size: small;">&nbsp;</span><a href="https://portal.iata.org/ISSP_Login" style="font-size: small;">Customer Portal</a><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: small;">&nbsp;and select the "</span><span style="font-size: small;"><font><b><font color="#3333ff">Join BSP/CASS</font></b><font color="#330033">"</font></font></span><span style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0); font-size: small;">&nbsp;functionality. In case you do not see that option, please refer to the detailed User Guide available in our ‘<b>Resources</b>’ tab of the</span><span style="font-size: small;">&nbsp;</span><a href="https://portal.iata.org/ISSP_Login" style="font-size: small;">Customer Portal</a><span style="font-size: small;">&nbsp;for further clarification.&nbsp;</span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2">&nbsp; b) When starting this functionality, you will have access to the country requirements applicable for the selected operation. Alternatively, the country requirements can also be found in on the Resource Center available on <font color="#000099"><u>www.iata.org/cs</u>.</font>&nbsp;</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2">&nbsp; c) Once the online joining process is submitted to IATA, our dedicated team will validate the local bank account mandate, resolution agreements (if applicable) and your airline’s compliance with the country requirements, and get back to you as soon as possible.</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></div><div><font face="arial" size="2" style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);">Do not hesitate in having a look at our video tutorial&nbsp;</font><span style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;"><b style="color: rgb(0, 119, 192);"><a href="http://cl.s6.exct.net/?qs=f9fc730d6ae6506511ebfa6b735f3aca8272db2c64052dc9e30ea2d8dc9a57cb" title="CASS joining" style="font-family: Arial, sans-serif; font-size: 10pt;">CASS joining</a>&nbsp;</b>for further support.</span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2"><b><font color="#330099">B. The below set of documents are still required in paper format</font></b> and must be sent to IATA Geneva c/o Airline Participation so your application is processed:</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><ul><li><span style="font-size: small;"><b>Airline CASS Participation - Additional Requirements Form</b>: only if the selected country requires it</span></li><li><span style="font-size: small;"><b>Airline BSP - CASS Local Bank Account Mandate</b>: For settlement purposes your Airline must provide IATA with a Banking Mandate for each CASS country. The applicable bank mandate and further instructions may be found within the online joining form.&nbsp;</span></li><li><span style="font-size: small;"><i>Alternatively to a local bank account</i>, your airline may opt for crossborder payment via ICCS. Should you wish to apply to ICCS in a specific operation, please log a query through our&nbsp;<a href="https://portal.iata.org/ISSP_Login">Customer Portal</a>&nbsp;which will be directly handlded by our ICCS&nbsp;team.</span></li></ul></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2">&nbsp;</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2">&nbsp;</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#330099"><b>C. Resolution Agreements:</b></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2">&nbsp;</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><ul><li><span style="font-size: small;">All IATA NON Member must send a Form of Application and Concurrence for the respective CASS operation;</span></li><li><span style="font-size: small;">Should the CASS participant be a GSSA, the GSSA must sign and submit the Counterindemnity, Form of Application and Concurrence, and Form of Authorization;</span></li><li><span style="font-size: small;">Updated versions of resolution documents (Counterindemnity or Form of Application and Concurrence) might be requested as well during the joining process);</span></li><li><span style="font-size: small;">If your airline is joining a CASS operation for the first time, you will need to submit the Counterindemnity &nbsp;and the Form of Application and Concurrence.</span></li></ul></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2">We recommend that you attach into the online joining process scan copies of the forms for review prior to sending the original documents.&nbsp;</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2">&nbsp;</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2"><b>Note</b>: The process will only begin once the above mentioned documents in (B) and (C) are received in paper format at the Geneva Head Office at the below address:</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2">&nbsp;</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2">International Air Transport Association</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2">c/o Global Airline Participation Team</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2">33, Route de l'Aéroport</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2">1215 Geneva 15 Airport</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2">Switzerland</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2">&nbsp;</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2"><br></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2" color="#330099"><b>D. Joining Fees:</b></font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2">&nbsp;</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><ul><li><span style="font-size: small;">A Joining Fee in USD is required to be paid before an Airline can be activated in the designated CASS.</span></li><li><span style="font-size: small;">Please access Airline Central Billing related information through our <a href="https://portal.iata.org/ISSP_Login">Customer Portal</a> . Once logged, please select <b><i>Resources</i></b>, then click on <b><i>Documents</i></b>. You would be able to do a research query if required.</span></li><li><span style="font-size: small;">Payment Procedure: Once the applicable original documents have been received and validated by IATA, an invoice will be issued to the airline. If the airline is an IATA Clearing House member, then the joining fee will be invoiced and settled through this option. &nbsp;Otherwise, a prepayment advise (Joining fee invoice) will be sent to you by email for your immediate payment by bank transfer. &nbsp;In such case, the instructions for payment are included in this prepayment advice.</span></li></ul><span style="font-size: small;"><div><span style="font-size: small;"><b><br></b></span></div><b>Is there anything else we can do for you?</b> We invite you to contact us through our&nbsp;</span><a href="https://portal.iata.org/ISSP_Login" style="font-size: small;">Customer Portal</a><span style="font-size: small;">&nbsp;&nbsp;and we will respond to you at the earliest.</span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><span style="font-size: small;"><br></span></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2">Before logging a query, please also review our <a href="https://portal.iata.org/faq_home?MainNav=resources&amp;subNav=faq&amp;mid=M2S1">FAQ section</a>. It contains relevant documentation and information regarding IATA processes &amp; procedures.</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2">&nbsp;</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2">We look forward to hearing from you shortly.</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2">&nbsp;</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2">Thank you,</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2">&nbsp;</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial" size="2">{!Case.OwnerFullName},</font></div><div style="color: rgb(0, 0, 0);"><font face="arial">&nbsp;</font></div>]]></td>
</tr>
